ied with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Robert Lawsoune was born about 1605, in Scotland. She had at least 1 daughter with Robert Lawsoune."},"et":{"about 1605–":"umbes 1605–Surnud","1605–Male":"1605–Surnud","1625–Female":"1625–Surnud","1605–Female":"1605–Surnud","about 1605":"umbes 1605","19 July 1625":"19. juuli 1625","1605":"1605","1625":"1625","Scotland":"Scotland","Liberton, Midlothian, Scotland":"Liberton, Midlothian, Scotland"},"fi":{"about 1605–":"noin 1605–Kuollut","1605–Male":"1605–Kuollut","1625–Female":"1625–Kuollut","1605–Female":"1605–Kuollut","about 1605":"noin 1605","19 July 1625":"19. heinäkuuta 1625","1605":"1605","1625":"1625","Scotland":"Scotland","Liberton, Midlothian, Scotland":"Liberton, Midlothian, Scotland"},"fr":{"about 1605–":"environ 1605–Décédée","1605–Male":"1605–Décédé","1625–Female":"1625–Décédée","1605–Female":"1605–Décédée","about 1605":"environ 1605","19 July 1625":"19 juillet 1625","1605":"1605","1625":"1625","Scotland":"Écosse","Liberton, Midlothian, Scotland":"Liberton, Midlothian, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Robert Lawsoune est née environ 1605, à Écosse. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Robert Lawsoune."},"de":{"about 1605–":"um 1605–Verstorben","1605–Male":"1605–Verstorben","1625–Female":"1625–Verstorben","1605–Female":"1605–Verstorben","about 1605":"um 1605","19 July 1625":"19. Juli 1625","1605":"1605","1625":"1625","Scotland":"Scotland","Liberton, Midlothian, Scotland":"Liberton, Midlothian, Scotland","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Robert Lawsoune wurde um 1605 in Scotland geboren. Sie hatte mit Robert Lawsoune mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"about 1605–":"about 1605–Desed